data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` construction **won't compile**. The good news: it becomes trivial.

```csharp
// .NET 10 — just use a normal lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the expression-tree plumbing.

---

### 2. Complex types — column name uniquification & nested path changes

Two separate changes will generate migrations that **rename your columns**:

- **Same-named properties across complex types** (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Complex_NestedComplex_Property` instead of `NestedComplex_Property` (e.g. `Payment_BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin the old names explicitly so no migration renames occur:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // repeat for other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested: Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

After configuring, run `dotnet ef migrations add VerifyNoChanges` — it should produce an empty migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on the interface now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your implementation won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL safe for logging
{
    // Use logCommandText for log output (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
}
```

Apply the same parameter addition to every other method you implement (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
